        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">At just <span class="text-white font-medium">3 tiles</span>, SUB is the shortest productive prefix in competitive Scrabble. You keep 4 tiles free for completions — that's more flexibility than OVER (4 tiles), UNDER (5 tiles), or INTER (5 tiles). This makes SUB bingos statistically easier to draw into.</p>
      </div>

      <p>The B tile (worth 3 points) also adds baseline value. Every SUB word starts with a guaranteed 5 points (S=1, U=1, B=3) before you add anything else. Compare that to RE- (1+1=2 pts) or UN- (1+1=2 pts).</p>

